    review_notes richText [note: 'business desc: Internal notes added by reviewer., technical desc: Type: richText, field ID: fldUCwNbON6q9J5qj']
    use_digital checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the campaign intends to use Digital media., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fldY0c3snhZkTJg9m']
    use_tv checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the campaign intends to use TV media., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fldYFhulETK12NIcO']
    use_radio checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the campaign intends to use Radio media., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fldBwaNwZ2u4Gc7Q8']
    use_print checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the campaign intends to use Print media., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fldDBrFY6Gbth8ysF']
    use_unconventional checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the campaign intends to use Unconventional media., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fld1jARxgeO5Xtiju']
    use_other checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the campaign intends to use Other types of media., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fldA0gfi6estfxXDA']
    other_media_types richText [note: 'business desc: Optional field where the client can specify any additional media types not covered in the standard media placement options. Enables flexibility for unconventional requests and ensures the campaign brief captures all relevant execution preferences., technical desc: Type: richText, field ID: fldIRygAjeTPotKby']
    digital_percentage percent [note: 'business desc: Percentage of the total budget allocated to Digital media., technical desc: Type: percent, field ID: fldBSVcsp7Oqs49aS']
    tv_percentage percent [note: 'business desc: Percentage of the total budget allocated to TV media., technical desc: Type: percent, field ID: fldtZZ9ECtV089iBj']
    radio_percentage percent [note: 'business desc: Percentage of the total budget allocated to Radio media., technical desc: Type: percent, field ID: fldfpcTb6P4Wo4guT']
    print_percentage percent [note: 'business desc: Percentage of the total budget allocated to Print media., technical desc: Type: percent, field ID: fld1PRpriQEuHvmAY']
    unconventional_percentage percent [note: 'business desc: Percentage of the total budget allocated to Unconventional media., technical desc: Type: percent, field ID: fldNGvvvIe6cWWVKU']
    other_percentage percent [note: 'business desc: Percentage of the total budget allocated to Other media., technical desc: Type: percent, field ID: fldkBJlHJzxw4SEaA']
    reviewed_by singleCollaborator [note: 'business desc: User who reviewed and updated the project brief., technical desc: Type: singleCollaborator, field ID: fldZAaINXkQj2c3LB']
    created createdTime [note: 'business desc: Timestamp automatically captured when the record is first created, supporting audit trails and chronological tracking., technical desc: Type: createdTime, field ID: fld1zjTrLvhT86dVi']
    media_allocation_validation formula [note: 'business desc: Validates whether the total media allocation exceeds 100%. Displays a red warning if the combined percentages of all selected media types surpass 100%. Used for preventing over-allocation of campaign budgets., technical desc: Type: formula, field ID: fldiMvR9NmkMLlftz']
    last_modified_by lastModifiedBy [note: 'business desc: Automatically records the user who made the most recent update to the project brief. Useful for tracking collaboration and accountability., technical desc: Type: lastModifiedBy, field ID: fldnpuzHDn822OSDK']
    campaign_creative_assets checkbox [note: 'business desc: Indicates whether the client will provide creative assets for the campaign. If not selected, the internal design team will generate artwork based on campaign requirements., technical desc: Type: checkbox, field ID: fldHa98n7CGFUtRP8']
    last_modified lastModifiedTime [note: 'business desc: Timestamp that reflects the most recent update to the record, enabling version tracking and operational visibility., technical desc: Type: lastModifiedTime, field ID: fldjNeKge7EwhD3Le']
    id autoNumber [note: 'business desc: Unique identifier., technical desc: Type: autoNumber, field ID: fldgoRDCTyjheljsZ']
    actual_q formula [note: 'business desc: This formula compares the quarter of {start_date} to the current quarter (based on TODAY()) within the same year. It returns:

Q0 if the date is in the same quarter as the current one.

Q-1, Q-2, or Q-3 if it is 1, 2, or 3 quarters earlier, respectively.

An empty value if it falls outside that range or in a different year.

Use this to determine which quarter (relative to the current quarter) a record belongs to—helpful for segmenting or tracking past events within the current year.

, technical desc: Type: formula, field ID: fldzuVqYAYDlwIoA8']
    quarter_of_the_year formula [note: 'business desc: his formula determines the quarter (Q1, Q2, Q3, or Q4) for the date in {start_date} and appends the respective year. The first part uses the month to calculate which quarter the date falls into; the second part adds the four-digit year. As a result, regardless of whether the date is in a past, current, or future year, you’ll see the quarter followed by the year, such as “Q3 2022” or “Q1 2025.” This is useful for quickly identifying the specific quarter and year of any given date., technical desc: Type: formula, field ID: fldjLnAk3DgCMNG3l']
    active_campaign multipleRecordLinks [note: 'business desc: This relationship connects a record to its associated active campaign.  It links campaigns to relevant records., technical desc: Type: multipleRecordLinks, Reference to active_campaign table, field ID: fldF9LH2bpo56VWSR']
    ai_context aiText [note: 'business desc: Generates a JSON object containing key campaign details from specified fields., technical desc: Type: aiText, field ID: fldRkQ6VkcfWTWvtp']
    clients multipleRecordLinks [note: 'business desc: This field connects orders to their clients.  Provides order context., technical desc: Type: multipleRecordLinks, Reference to clients table, field ID: fldyVuxzYgthhEE4D']
    note: '### project_brief Table (airtable id: tblkmpqL98s7MydEh) - This table has 50 fields - This table consolidates all necessary data for evaluating and processing campaign briefs submitted by clients. It includes contact information, campaign details, target demographics, media preferences, geography targeting, and workflow status. This structure ensures standardized data collection, review, and collaboration for streamlined campaign approval   and execution workflows within the Grassroots CRM platform.'
}

